PiperOrigin-RevId: 327471874

[tfds] Remove config name text datasets

As TFDS text encoding API has many bug, performance issues and is unsupported, we are cleaning up our datasets to remove all encoder builder config and only keep the plain text version of the datasets.

To use encoder, please use `tensorflow_text` which is a more flexible, more supported, performant text encoding API.

For forward compatibility, `tfds.load('ds/plain_text')` -> `tfds.load('ds')` will load the default plain text dataset.

Option to make transformer more identical to the original.
In the attention layer, scale down the logits explicitly, instead of folding the scaling into the parameter initialization.  This makes no difference for adafactor, which multiplies the updates by the parameter scale, but is likely to make a difference for other optimizers.

Simplify the handling of LazyAllreduceSum:
  - add a MeshImpl.slicewise_delay_allreduce method which is like MeshImpl.slicewise, but delays allreduce if possible - i.e. it outputs a LazyAllreduceSum object if all the arguments are also LazyAllReduceSum objects.  This method is called when lowering sum operations.  Also invoke this method when lowering reshape operations, which fixes a performance bug in model-parallel Transformer.  In the future, it would be good to have some principled way of deciding when to delay allreduce, or if we didn't need to because XLA rewrote/optimized this for us.
